Bring a large #pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Remove and discard any large stems from @kale{4%ounce}; chop half the leaves into
bite-size pieces (all for 4 servings). Dice @roma tomato{1} into ¼-inch pieces.
Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}. Quarter @lemon{1}.

Once water is boiling, add @fresh tomato ricotta ravioli{9%ounce} to pot.
Immediately reduce to a low simmer. Cook, stirring occasionally, until ravioli
are tender and floating to the top, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Reserve ½ cup pasta cooking water, then drain and set aside.

Meanwhile, heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a large pan over
medium-high heat. Add chopped kale and tomato; season with @Tuscan Heat Spice{1%tablespoon}
half the Tuscan Heat Spice (all for 4 servings), @salt{¼%tsp} (½ tsp for 4), and
a pinch of @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender,
~{5-7%minutes}.

Add garlic; cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @veggie stock concentrate{1} and ¼ cup reserved pasta cooking water
(1⁄3 cup for 4); cook, stirring, until sauce has thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Remove from heat; stir in @cream cheese{2%tablespoon}, @butter{2%tablespoon}
(4 TBSP for 4), and a squeeze of lemon juice until melted and combined.

> TIP: If sauce seems too thick, stir in more reserved pasta cooking water a
> splash at a time.

Gently stir drained ravioli into pan with sauce until coated.

Divide ravioli between #plates{} and serve with remaining lemon wedges on the
side.